
IO Exercise:

***** For security reasons at permissions for IO collection
      have been turned off.

The pio.c code performs parallel IO to a single file.
It mimics the creation of a checkpoint/restart file
and subsequently updates it 29 more time.

    You will build the pio executable.
    You run it with remora to acquire details about the execution.

    You can run it without remora, to make sure all is working.
*******************************************************************************

1.)
    Start a session:

       idev            #wait for prompt, accept reservation and all defaults
                       #You will automatically have an MPI environment
       cd remora_ex/io

2.) Note:  look at pio.c; it uses MPI-IO to write to files and is complicated.
           All you need to know it that it writes to files in scratch.
           (BTW, it also uses IOPS through the File System that pio executes in.)

3.) Build pio

       make            # makes pio


4.)
    There is a job script (named "job"), which you could submit from the login 
    to run the pio executable.  It sets up the file system for 4-way striping.

    Here we will use it as an executable script and run it interactively 
    (just the unix commands are executed, nice!).
    You might look at the job script to see how it is setting up to run 
    (in batch or interactively).

       ./job

5.) The script cd's to $SCRATCH/pio_test/4 where it is executed, and therefore
    the remora_# directory exists there.  Copy it back to your present directory
    after executing the script.

       cp -rp $SCRATCH/pio_test/4/remora* .


